It’s hard to imagine a set that inspires more fan curiosity (read: obsession) than that of a Star Wars movie.
Its net worth is in the billions, and the universe is likely to keep growing long, long after your lifetime.
As Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker’s second unit director, and the first woman to ever hold the megaphone on a Star Wars movie, Mahoney got to experience all of it.
So, from a person who very much oughta know, here’s what you experience while directing a Star Wars movie.
Being on a Star Wars Set Never Gets OldIf you thought even space opera scenery would get humdrum after seeing it all day, every day for months, think again.